    RailsBump is useful if you're planning to upgrade your Rails app to the next major version. It lets you check an individual Ruby gem or a whole Bundler lockfile (Gemfile.lock) for compatibility with all major and minor Rails versions since Rails 4.0.
    %br
    Read more about how it works and the history of this project
    = link_to 'on GitHub', 'https://github.com/manuelmeurer/railsbump', target: '_blank'
    and please
    = link_to 'open an issue', 'https://github.com/manuelmeurer/railsbump/issues', target: '_blank'
    if you encounter a problem.

